I don't know if that's what I expected.
If, at the age of 18, I was supposed to understand that governance could contradict the political campaigns that preceded it.
Obviously, the electoral function is not predictable, because the opposition political party and events that happen by chance, such as the Newton massacre, influence our public conversation.
However, all the examples I have listed above seem to be largely the choice of administration.
That's what bothers me the most.
I voted for Obama again in 2012, but not because I was excited about his candidacy.
Mitt Romney presented a confused and unrefined alternative that did not seem to allow for the determination of his policies or positions.
I felt that Obama, elected for a second term by being freed from the pressure of future elections, would keep the promises that we had been hearing for so long.
Yet, while the positive opinion index dropped below 45% this week, it is even more difficult to return to 2008 through this book.
He makes me wish for the many promises that have gone away.
